@Node Intro "Introduction to <NameUnknown>"

                 <NnameUnknown> (C) 1994 Hydra!/TensioN

  Well, I don't know about you but I've tried millions of ANSI editors and
  they all seem to be lacking in some respect or other,  some are great to
  work with but don't create correct ISO ANSI, others are crap but create
  correct ANSI files.  So I wrote <NameUnknown> to solve this dilemma!

  PlusEd, is a great ansi editor with plenty of features but it does not
  create correct ansi that displays on everything.

  Fansi is an OK Editor, but just lacks quite a few needed features

  DIED is the ANSI editor i use as it's pretty quick and generates nearly
  perfect ansi if it wasn't for the 2 amiga-only control codes at the top
  and bottom of every file.

  Hyperansi is a bit drab and featureless.. (but some like it)

  TextPaint is my favourite ansi editor as it was GREAT to use and had some
  REALLY nice features like scrolling the background or forground by a
  character in either direction and the abilty to draw lines and boxes etc.
  the only problem with this is the output it creates! it would only display
  in a CLI window,  you try getting a PC to recognise most of it's ansi
  codes!

  So now you've got this lovely new program sitting in front of you and
  you're thinking "Wow! This Should Be Cool!".  So go and have a look at
  the @{"feature list!" link features}

@EndNode

@Node features "Features"

  Features
  ========

  <Name Unknown> has more features than some of the best ansi editors around
  at the moment,  here's a few of the better ones!

  * Multiple ANSI files open at one time,  NO OTHER ANSI EDITOR can do this.

  * You can cut and paste between them! Yeah!

  * Creates ISO 6429 Compiant ANSI files that should work with ANYTHING that
    supports STANDARD ansi. (of course you can change the way it outputs
    files greatly by using the Output Options section)

  * Uses standard clipboard so you can cut/paste between your text editor
    and <Name Unknown>

  * Fully Dynamic Memory Allocation of screens with NO LIMIT to the amount of
    ansi files you have open at one time!

  * Uses ReqTools.library for file requesters!

  * Lets YOU pick the screen mode!  (great for peeps like me with multisync
    monitors!)

  * Workbench 2/3 Look, no horrible looking gadgets!

  * Full Paint Mode, allowing you to draw boxes, circles, triangles, lines
    etc..

  of course there are MANY more features to list but it'd take far too long
  for me to list them all!  Just have a look the menus if you don't beleive
  me!

@EndNode

@Node Installation  "Installation"

  Installation
  ============

  All you have to do is make sure you have reqtools.library in LIBS:
  and just run <NameUnknown> by Double Clicking It's Icon!

  It couldn't be simpler.

@EndNode

@Node Distribution "Distribution"

  Distribution
  ============

  Firstly,please DON'T Sell this program so you can make money from it!
  if anyone's gona make any money from it then it's gonna be me!

  <NameUnknown> Is FREE Software! (subsequent versions WILL be shareware
  so check first) and can be distributed to wherever you like, and however
  you like just so long as all it's files remain intact and unmodified!

  Please, if you are going to put this program on a cover disk or subscriber
  disk then let me know!  I don't mind, I'd just like the curtisy!
  (Unlike Amiga Shopper who put my XMASH program on a subsriber disk and
  didn't even bother to tell me or even send me a free copy!)

  Also I'd like to hear from any PD distributors who include this program
  in thier library or from CD-ROM makers.  Like I say, I don't mind it
  being distributed, I'd just like to know by WHO.

  So Please @{"Contact Me" link Author} first!

@EndNode

