@Node Instructions "Instructions"

  Instructions
  ============

  Shit, where do i start ?  Hmm...  ok here's a few pointers for peeps who've
  just loaded it up!

  1) When you open a NEW file or LOAD a file the screen you are working on
     is still in memory,  use the menus/screens/list to select which screen
     you want to edit when one or more files are open

  2) Check the output options before saving files as it will default to the
     smallest file size settings. for PC's you might have to enable the CR
     at the end of each line...

  3) Um......  Um......  Nope, I can't think of anything else that's really
     important at the mo..

  <more docs later when i get round to writing them, volounteers welcome!>

@EndNode

@Node BetaNotes "Beta Notes"

This is a list of features that ansied supports, I'll keep adding things to
the top of the list along with a date from now on so you can see what's
new and what to test for me,  PLEASE if you find any bugs gimme a ring
on 0202 434858 (voice,ask for Dom) or leave a msg the BBS...

23-11-94
  Copy function on edit menu works now

  B-MARK button and Mark BlockMenu Option work, to mark a block first move
  the cursor to the topleft of the block, then click b-mark, then click bottom
  right of the block and click b-mark again,  the area selected gets copied
  to the clipboard as soon as you let go of b-mark..

  at the mo you can't paste it back in and it only copies plain ascii text
  as the clipboard only supports iff data, and i've got to design a new iff
  format for ansitext (with colours and styles..)

  There was a bug in the Save ANSI As routine (save ansi was ok) in that
  after saving the ansi as the specified filename it would copy the filename
  string to the window title on the toolbox, but i forgot to allocate more
  memory if the string was longer than the old filename, so it sometimes
  crashed..  but it's all ok now.

  I've not found any enforcer hits (illegal mem accessing) or other bugs that
  make it crash, so if you find any LET ME KNOW ASAP AS THESE CAN BE BITCHES
  TO FIND and the smaller my source the easier it is to find em now :-)


  You'll notice that pressing return now goes to the next line.. instead of
  printing a square box on the screen.

  italics and bold still don't show on the actual screen text (but are loaded
  and saved correctly) but if text is in bold or italic and you move the cursor
  overit you'll see 2 small dots at the bottom right of the character under
  the cursor.

  The DI-ED Mode is nearly finished. if you've used died you'll know how this
  works, if not then you'll see :-)

  The paint mode works correctly now,  just click colours and then click mouse
  pointer on screen and charater under mouse changes style and colour to the
  current settings, so you can select a background other than black and
  draw nicely on the screen,  this mode is *REALLY* handy for quickly adding
  colour into logos as I'm sure you will find after trying it.

  Most of the menu functions still dont work, but they are getting there..

  Ok, that's it for this version...  till next time..

@EndNode
